If checked, the matching will be done on the path alias for the translation in the default language.
For example, if your default language is English and your news articles have paths that start with /news/ then you can enable this option and provide |^/news/.+| as the regular expression. The rule would then also be applied to the translated news articles with paths /fr/nouvelles/* and /nl/nieuws/*.
